Hi friends. 💕🌜

Most recently I have been traveling back home to Honduras, most of you don’t know this but parts of Honduras are extremely underserved so I am reaching out to my current Lunastry community to help another community in need. 

We aren’t asking for you to displace yourself, maybe to donate items that you may have an excess of or in no need of anymore. 

The families of El Diviso in Honduras could really use the following items:

- Gently used clothing 
- Hygiene essentials
- Feminine Products
- School supplies
- Toys
- Canned goods

The most underserved in the community are the children, they are missing out of school days due to lack of supplies, backpacks and basic essentials such as clean clothes. There is the option of sponsorship for children. The currency exchange is 24 Honduran Lempiras for every $1 , thus your dollar going a very long way. 

Currently Lunastry is taking donations up until March 17. 
Items can be dropped off, or a donation can be made in your name. 

Your help, thoughts and consideration is the most important part in helping a community in need. The village of El Diviso and Lunastry thanks you!

Please like and share 💕💕

“ Take a step back today and look at all of those beautiful things you have “ 

I want to thank everyone who donated items for Honduras 🇭🇳. Your kindness goes unnoticed and I know the universe will multiply it for you. The kids were extremely happy and very grateful. Some of them were too shy to even accept their gifts. 

I didn’t get around to taking videos and photos of the adults receiving clothing/items, it was a bit chaotic and I honestly felt uncomfortable recording them. But I promise to make a bigger effort next time. This is something I’ve been wanting to do for years and finally got around to it. Looking forward to more grateful moments like this. The beginning of something amazing. 

I also had issues with transporting things in my luggage because they thought I was selling them and had to declare them. So the next load will be shipped out, which can take 3-5 weeks. So if you have any clothing/items you want to get rid of please feel free to drop them off at the store, they can use anything and everything.

I asked what else they made need for the school, they need fans (extremely hot in there) some art for the kids, curtains and freshly painted walls. So my next trip I plan to buy all of that, if anyone would like to donate some $ please DM me. I plan to leave 2nd week in April. I also want to paint some art on the inside and outside of the school, this will be an amazing and fairly big project to do with a group. If anyone is willing to fly out there for a weekend. Please DM me, you’ll just need to cover your flight and I can cover your food and boarding. This project is just for the kindergarten school, which teaches 12 children. The bigger school I plan to help in the near future and has 80 students. 

Thank you SO much from the bottom of our hearts ❤️

Full Moon in Capricorn tonight. Full Moons are a time for releasing and relinquishing. If you have an excess in your life, this is the time for it to go down the drain. Through silent meditation, exchanging of thoughts, or spiritual practice, Full Moons are a point when we can let go.

To align with a Capricorn Full Moon, we need to exit the comfortable emotional shell associated with Cancer (aka the Crab). Rather, we should set our sights on  attacking something on a long-standing “To Do” list, whether that relates to work, family, communication, or a doctor’s appointment. The goal here: do something that has material, tangible results. Capricorn is an earth sign, it’s not for airy plans or watery feelings.  Happy Full Moon Luna Babes!
